Jo must have fallen asleep, for suddenly Laurie's ghost seemed to stand before her.
But then he bent down and kissed her.
The she knew himm, and flew up, crying joyfully.
"Oh my Teddy! Oh my Teddy!"
"Dear Jo, you are glad to see me, then?"
"Glad! My blessed boy, words can't express my gladness, Where's Amy?"
"Your monther has got her down at Meg's. We stopped there by the way, and there was no getting my wife away from them."
